blog.name: skeleton-richard
blog.title: a million choices, though little on their own
blog.description:
Mostly the Middle Ages, books, and religion (with some Shakespeare and American history and bad jokes in between). I dedicated my life to the 15th century French poet, Charles d'Orleans and to the reading of strange manuscripts and someday I'll be important enough to have access to them at the British Library. I also like paleontology and deer and Anne de Bretagne. In this house we love and and respect Bonne d'Armagnac. [Fyodor, queer Christian and reclusive historian, crepynge beeste of lyuynge soule since sometime in the early 90s] 
All hail the Thrips.

summary: I’ve seen the recent increase of interest in the RSC Richard II with David Tennant and I just want to welcome you all to the...
body: I’ve seen the recent increase of interest in the RSC Richard II with David Tennant and I just want to welcome you all to the fandom and hope you enjoy your time in this sad glittery king hell! Seriously though, welcome to all newcomers and anyone just interested in it, it’s a fantastic play and I’m glad to share it with even more people. We have a lot of fanfiction on Ao3 and listed here if you need fic. Cheers!

summary: i feel like everything about david tennant's protrail of crowley, from the slutty goth costuming to the yearning gay acting...
body:
i feel like everything about david tennant’s protrail of crowley, from the slutty goth costuming to the yearning gay acting choices, was specifically designed to make me suffer for having not really been into him back when he was in doctor who

i missed the thirsting after david tennant boat back when it first sailed in 2012 and now i must be punished with a perfect character who i can both lust after and project my entire personality on to and honestly it’s not fair
